properties.name: Eiffel Tower
properties.description: Posted by Brent623Paris, France The Eiffel Tower is an iron tower built on the Champ de Mars beside the Seine River in Paris, France. The tower has become a global icon of France and is one of the most recognizable structures in the world. Named after its designer, engineer Gustave Eiffel, the Eiffel Tower is the tallest building in Paris. More than 200,000,000 have visited the tower since its construction in 1889, including 6,719,200 in 2006, making it the most visited paid monument in the world. Including the 79 ft antenna, the structure is 1,063 ft high, which is equivalent to about 81 levels in a conventional building.

properties.name: Eiffel Tower
properties.description: Posted by Chef27Paris, France The Eiffel Tower is an immense structure of exposed latticework supports made of iron. It took 300 steel workers and 2 years to construct it. There are 15,000 iron pieces and 2.5 million rivots. It is 986 feet tall without the antenna. It weighs 8.56 million kg. There are 1671 steps to the top of the tower.

properties.description: Posted by RainsParis, France The Eiffel Tower was built for the 1889 International Exhibition. The man who was behind this massive monument is Alexandre Gustave Eiffel. The tower was completed between March 28-31,1889. It took two years 2 months and 5 days to complete it. Only one worker was killed. I believe that the Eiffle tower is such a wonderful place of history it has been through a lot such as the tower has been painted 6 diff. colors that takes 50 tons of different shades of brown. The tower is 990 feet tall. It is a symbol of Paris known world wide. Usually when people go to Paris they definatly want to go to visit the Eiffel Tower and also watch its light show that appears just about every night.

properties.name: Eiffel Tower
properties.description: Posted by HannahalyssaParis, FranceThe Eiffel Tower located in Paris, France was built in May of 1889. It was built to celebrate the great strides that had been made in engineering and science. The Eiffel Tower was known as the worlds tallest building until around forty years later the Empire State was built. There are 2731 steps to the top of the tower, and it wieghs 7000 tons. The names of 72 french scientists are written just beneath the first platform. They are hard to notice in photographs, but can be seen clearly in person.

properties.name: Eiffel Tower
properties.description: Posted by Rosebud423Paris, FranceThe Eiffel Tower was designed by Gustave Eiffel and therefore named in honor of him. His design was unanimously chosen out of 700 designs entered in a competition. People developed mixed feelings about the Eiffel Tower. A petition of 300 names opposed to construction of the tower. Despite the oppposition, construction began in 1887. It was completed in 1889 for the Exhibition of Paris. The tower is made completely of iron and weighs 7000 tons. It reaches a height of 1,052 feet and was the tallest structure in the world until 1930 with the construction of the Chrysler Building. The Eiffel Tower was actually about to be destroyed in 1909 because it was accused of having no important use. It was saved due to its antenna used as a vital telegraphy service. Its antenna is also used for radio and television transmissions. The Eiffel Tower is now accepted by all the French people as an important French symbol.
